node.text: Porsche is in the minds of many the ultimate sports car brand. Its cars – especially its legendary 911 – blend high performance with quality construction and even a solid reputation for dependability. But the brand that made its name with small nimble two-door sports cars ruffled feathers in the automotive world when it tried its hand at a four-door sport utility vehicle, the Cayenne. Today, SUVs make up a huge chunk of Porsche’s sales. The brand is now entering the race toward electrification – but this time the innovator is playing catch-up to others.

node.title: How Porsche went from sports cars to SUVs ... and EVs

node.text: It’s taken over two years, but these days Jeremy Mateo is finally feeling at home. Mateo, 27, is a real estate broker in Honolulu, Hawaii, and bought his first condo on Oahu island right before the coronavirus pandemic in March 2020. Over the course of a year he saved $60,000 for a down payment and worked toward his goal of buying his “dream home.” Then he spent another year renovating and furnishing his place. The last of his furniture arrived in spring 2021, finally closing the chapter on his homebuying journey. Here’s how Mateo bought his one-bedroom condo for $560,000. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.text: Violence and mass shootings erupted over the weekend, and could continue. 274 mass shootings have occurred this year, with 304 dead, which is on pace for one of the most violent years in history. Here's what the country's outlook is.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 07, 2021. May be an image of ‎money and ‎text that says '‎13% of Americans traded crypto in the past year, survey finds ا CNBC‎'‎‎.

node.text:
Have you traded crypto recently?⁠
⁠
More than 1 in 10 Americans invested in cryptocurrency over the past year, according to a survey published by the University of Chicago, a sign of the popularity of digital currencies like bitcoin and ethereum. Specifically, 13% bought or traded crypto in the past 12 months — by comparison, 24% of Americans invested in stocks over the same time period, according to the survey.⁠
⁠
How much of your portfolio do financial advisors say you should allocate to crypto? Link in bio. ⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The ultra-wealthy have made full use of Roth individual retirement accounts Here's how you can do the same CNBC'.

node.text:
Sometimes, it can seem like only rich people can benefit from the tax code.⁠
⁠
Some ultra-wealthy individuals have amassed hundreds of millions — or even billions — of dollars in tax-sheltered Roth individual retirement accounts, according to a report released by ProPublica.⁠
⁠
However, the strategy is generally available to anyone who wants to use it.⁠
⁠
Details on that strategy – and how you can apply it to your own finances – at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 07, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, office and text that says '"There is no going back to the status quo": What the return to the office will look like this fall CNBC'.

node.text:
What is the solution for a return to the office during a global pandemic?⁠
⁠
Over a year into the pandemic 56% of Americans work closer to 56%, even though 61% say they prefer working from home.⁠ ⁠
⁠
Companies all around the world are planning to bring more workers back to the office. ⁠A survey of 350 business leaders by staffing firm LaSalle Network found that 70% plan to have employees back in the office in some capacity by the fall of this year.⁠
⁠
@CNBCMakeIt spoke with experts about what the return to work will look like. Link in bio to read more about it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Remove these 7 things from your resume "ASAP," says CEO who has read more than 1,000 resumes this year CNBC'.

node.text:
We constantly hear about what you should put on your resume, but we rarely talk about what to leave off.⁠
⁠
As the CEO of a resume writing service, @CNBCMakeIt contributor Peter Yang has read more than a thousand resumes this year so far, and he's seen a lot of “junk” that doesn’t belong — things that can hurt your chances of landing an interview.⁠
⁠
Visit the link in bio for seven commonly overlooked things you should remove from your resume ASAP — and why.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'United Airlines will require all u.S. employees to get Covid vaccines, a first for domestic carriers UNITED UNITED careO are CNBC'.

node.text:
United Airlines will require its 67,000 U.S. employees to get vaccinated against Covid by no later than Oct. 25 or risk termination, a first for major U.S. carriers that will likely ramp up pressure on rivals.⁠
⁠
Airlines including United have so far resisted vaccine mandates for all workers, instead offering incentives like extra pay or time off to get inoculated. Delta Air Lines in May started requiring newly hired employees to show proof of vaccination. United followed suit in June.⁠
⁠
Click on the link in bio to read more.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 06, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Payrolls ncrease 943,000 in July as unemployment rate slides to 5.4% PITTSBULER CNBC'.

node.text:
The July jobs report beat expectations, with hiring rising at its fastest pace in nearly a year.⁠
⁠
Nonfarm payrolls increased by 943,000 for the month while the unemployment rate dropped to 5.4%, according to the Labor Department’s Bureau of Labor Statistics. The payroll increase was the best since August 2020.⁠
⁠
Leisure and hospitality led job creation, adding 380,000 positions for the month, of which 253,000 came in bars and restaurants. ⁠
⁠
Read more at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"A lot of people with money don't have wealth": This expert says this is what makes you "wealthy" CNBC'.

node.text:
Very few people self-identify as upper middle class or wealthy — even if, by the numbers, their income or net worth puts them in that category.⁠
⁠
But it is not just income or even net worth that makes someone “wealthy,” experts say. That’s especially true when it comes to differentiations between the upper-middle class, the rich, and the truly wealthy, says Susan Bradley, a certified financial planner and the founder of Sudden Money Institute. ⁠
⁠
“Wealth to me is a much bigger, deeper experience,” she says. “And a lot of people with money don’t have wealth.”⁠
⁠
So, what does make you wealthy? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 05, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Uber CEO explains why he's mandating vaccines for office workers but not drivers Uber CNBC'.

node.text:
All of Uber’s U.S. employees will have to be vaccinated against the coronavirus before returning to the office later this year, but the company fell short on requiring an integral part of its business, its drivers, to get vaccinated.⁠
⁠
Click on the link in bio to read how CEO Dara Khosrowshahi explained his thinking. ⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 05, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robinhood retreats after monster rally this week as stockholders file to sell 97.9 million shares CNBC'.

node.text:
Robinhood is pulling back from its monster rally this week.⁠
⁠
The company says that existing stockholders will sell 97.9 million shares over time and that it will not receive any of the proceeds from the stock sale.⁠
⁠
The selling shareholders include a number of venture capital firms that invested in Robinhood early on. ⁠
⁠
Read more at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 04, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'If you say any of these 6 things during the job interview, don't expect to get an offer, says career expert CNBC'.

node.text:
Each and every little thing you say (yes, even just one sentence) during a job interview shapes whether or not a hiring manager thinks you are a strong fit for the job.⁠
⁠
That’s why it’s important to remind yourself in advance of what to resist saying. ⁠
⁠
Visit the link in bio for responses to avoid – and tips and examples of what to say instead. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 04, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Elon Musk says he plans to hold bitcoin long-term here's why that could be a good strategy CNBC'.

node.text:
Despite his criticism of bitcoin mining and its environmental impact, billionaire Elon Musk confirmed that he personally owns the cryptocurrency and has held it long-term.⁠
⁠
Though he didn’t specify exact amounts, Musk shared last week that bitcoin is his largest cryptocurrency holding, above ethereum and dogecoin. The Tesla and SpaceX CEO also said he has no plans to sell any of his bitcoin anytime soon.⁠
⁠
While investing in cryptocurrency is a risk, experts agree that a long-term holding strategy is the best practice. Details on risks and best practices when investing in cryptocurrency at the link in bio. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 04, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Target to pay 100% of college tuition and textbooks in bid to attract workers CNBC we're hiring! O.com/careers work some'.

node.text:
Target said Wednesday it will offer new perks to woo workers: a debt-free way to get a college degree and payments toward graduate programs.⁠
⁠
Starting this fall, the big-box retailer said it will cover the cost of tuition, fees and textbooks for part- and full-time workers who pursue a qualifying undergraduate degree at more than 40 institutions. ⁠
⁠
Click on the link in bio to read more.
